text: Pchegatlukay () is a rural locality (an aul) and the administrative center of Pchegatlukayskoye Rural Settlement of Teuchezhsky District, the Republic of Adygea, Russia. The population was 869 as of 2018. There are 21 streets. == Geography == The aul is Located on the left bank of the Psekups River, 5 km east from the city of Adygeysk. == Ethnicity == The aul is inhabited by Circassians. == References == Category:Rural localities in Teuchezhsky District
title: Pchegatlukay
